{"id":14881720,"mediaExerciseId":"e3e3ecfe-6138-4dd9-bee5-dce3b72f86b4","exerciseName":"10","chapterName":"20","chapterTitle":"Credit and Inventory Management","groupId":612458,"groupTitle":"Critical Thinking Questions","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":700,"solutions":[{"id":6043667,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this problem, we need to assess whether Dell has an advantage over other PS manufactures if any short inventory period. We also need to say why not all companies switch to this kind of management system if it is valuable. ","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"The company Dell uses JIP inventory management, whose primary goal is to keep inventory on hand exactly as needed. With this management system, Dell typically maintains a sales inventory for three to four days. Precisely because of this short period of inventory, Dell has the added advantage of quickly turning those inventories into sales, thus maximizing its turnover. \n\n","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"However, in order for such a business system to function and to avoid shortages of PS components, it is necessary that the company Dell has a strong high-level cooperation with its suppliers who will deliver all the necessary PS components without delay. \n","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"\nTherefore, if PS manufactures do not have strong and good cooperation with their suppliers, then they must not engage in such a JIP imventory management system and must increase their inventory.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4}],"ratin